      • getId

        public int getId(I thing)
        Get the id for the specified object.

        Don't hold onto the id across the world, it's being dynamically re-mapped as needed.

        Usually the name should be used instead of the id, if using the Block/Item object itself is not suitable for the task.

        Parameters:
        thing - Block/Item object.
        Returns:
        Block/Item id or -1 if it wasn't found.
